Category.Description: Features to control image improvement measures.

Category.Name: NonUniformityCorrection
Category.ToolTip: Control the removal of non-uniformity related artifacts.
Category.Description: Non-uniformity e.g. varies with the effective exposure time or sensor temperature. The non-uniformity correction provides various features to adapt to different conditions.

Category.Name: BackgroundCorrection
Category.ToolTip: Subtract a previously recorded correction image and/or add an offset.
Category.Description: Allows to subtract fixed pattern, e. g. by integrating a dark image as correction image. Can improve image quality.

Category.Name: DefectPixelCorrection
Category.ToolTip: Control the correction of defect pixels.
Category.Description: Defects will be replaced by a value calculated from non-defective neighborhood pixels.

Enumeration.Name: NUCMode
Enumeration.ToolTip: Controls the operating mode of the non-uniformity correction. Depending on the factory-provided correction data, different modes may be available.
Enumeration.Description: Controls the operating mode of the non-uniformity correction. Depending on the factory-provided correction data, different modes may be available.

EnumEntry.Name: Off
EnumEntry.ToolTip: Correction is inactive.
EnumEntry.Description: Image data is passed through unchanged.

EnumEntry.Name: TwoPoint
EnumEntry.ToolTip: Two point non-uniformity correction.
EnumEntry.Description: Uses a dark reference image and a bright reference image to calculate offset and gain for each pixel and correct the non-uniformity accordingly.

Integer.Name: NUCDatasetActive
Integer.ToolTip: The index of the active data set. The maximum value allowed depends on the number of valid data sets in the camera. The mapping of an index value to a specific correction data file may vary from camera to camera or after correction data modifications. Use the NUCDatasetSelector and corresponding features to retrieve more information about the data sets.
Integer.Description: The index of the active data set. The maximum value allowed depends on the number of valid data sets in the camera. The mapping of an index value to a specific correction data file may vary from camera to camera or after correction data modifications. Enumeration.ToolTip: Operation mode of the automatic adaption to varying sensor operating conditions.
Enumeration.Description: Controls automatic selection of the NUCDatasetActive.

EnumEntry.Name: Off
EnumEntry.ToolTip: Automatic mode is inactive.
EnumEntry.Description: The data set needs to be selected externally.

EnumEntry.Name: Once
EnumEntry.ToolTip: Single shot automatic.
EnumEntry.Description: Selects the data set automatically once at the next exposure.

EnumEntry.Name: Continuous
EnumEntry.ToolTip: Continuous automatic.
EnumEntry.Description: Selects the data set at every exposure.

Command.Description: Activate the data set currently selected by NUCDatasetSelector.

Float.Description: Sensor temperature, in degree Celsius, at acquisition of the currently activated data set. The data set should be selected, so that the actual sensor temperature is close to the reference temperature.

Integer.Description: Selects a data point of a data set for access to its properties. The maximum value allowed depends on the number of valid data points in the data set.

Integer.Name: NUCDatasetNodeValue
Integer.ToolTip: Setpoint value of the selected data point indexed by NUCDatasetNodeSelector. The setpoint defines the mean value which the corrected image will have if the input image has a mean value of the corresponding correction data image.

EnumEntry.Description: Integrate BCIntegrationFrameCount frames after BCIntegration start.

Enumeration.Description: Controls the operating mode of the background correction. Different modes may be available, depending on the previously integrated correction data.

EnumEntry.Name: Off
EnumEntry.ToolTip: Correction is inactive.
EnumEntry.Description: Image data is passed through unchanged.

EnumEntry.Name: On
EnumEntry.ToolTip: Current correction image is subtracted from image and the BCDatasetOffsetValue is added.

EnumEntry.Name: OffsetOnly
EnumEntry.ToolTip: Just adds the (signed) BCDatasetOffsetValue.
EnumEntry.Description: Can be used as general purpose level shift.

EnumEntry.Name: ReferenceImage
EnumEntry.ToolTip: Outputs the current correction reference image.
EnumEntry.Description: For testing purposes. By selecting this option the background correction will become an image source.

Enumeration.Description: Shows the current state of the background correction processing. If the state is Ok then the BC is operating normally as configured with BCMode, otherwise the ROI settings might be out of range, a new integration might be needed or is still in progress.
